TypeSignature.Value: .class public auto ansi beforefieldinit ChangeTokenTooEarlyException extends Microsoft.Office.Server.UserProfiles.UserProfileException

Docs.summary: Represents an exception that is thrown when a user requests changes since a particular point in time, but that point in time is older than the earliest change on record.

remarks.para: A change token represents a point in time in the user profile store. generally keeps two weeks worth of user profile store change history.

The exception is thrown when a user requests changes since a particular point in time, but that point in time is older than the earliest change on record. Therefore, Office SharePoint Server 2007 cannot provide all changes since that point in time. If you are using the change token to keep changes in sync, then you should perform a full synchronization instead.
